<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
'On the Way to the Forum' on the Way: Officials from the Orange County 
Performing Arts Center and the La Jolla Playhouse announced Tuesday that they 
will collaborate on a revival of "A Funny Thing Happened on the Way to the 
Forum." 
</P>
<P>
The 1962 "Forum," with the book by Burt Shevelove and Larry Gelbart and the 
first musical to have score and lyrics by Stephen Sondheim, will play for six 
weeks at the Playhouse's 492-seat Mandell Weiss Theatre (July 3 to Aug. 12) and 
two weeks at the 2,996-seat Center (Aug. 17-26). Des McAnuff, artistic director 
of the La Jolla Playhouse, will direct. No cast has been announced. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Sondheim 
