260 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROYAL RUNS WIN STREAK TO 22 MATCHES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JIM COLEMAN, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Royal High boys' volleyball Coach Bob Ferguson thought 1990 was going to be a 
rebuilding year. 
</P>
<P>
Maybe he meant the Highlanders were going to add on another Southern Section 
championship. 
</P>
<P>
Royal, the defending Southern Section 2-A Division champion, won its 22nd 
consecutive match Tuesday and fifth this season, upending visiting Crespi in 
three games, 15-3, 15-12, 15-3. 
</P>
<P>
The Highlanders, 38-4 since the inception of their volleyball program three 
years ago, have won all 24 of their home matches. 
</P>
<P>
"Our streak is still alive," Ferguson said afterward. "We're actually probably 
better now than we were last year at this time. Everything we tried today 
worked." 
</P>
<P>
Crespi will vouch for that. The Celts (4-1) trailed by just 4-3 in the first 
game when Royal broke away, capitalizing on Crespi mistakes to score the final 
11 points. 
</P>
<P>
The Celts collected themselves in the next game and led, 12-8, behind Mike 
Palumbo's five kills. But Royal scored seven points in a row to win the game. 
</P>
<P>
In the third game Royal, behind Jeff Colton's five kills, jumped to a 9-1 lead 
and coasted to the win. 
</P>
<P>
"The big factor was they played better defense than we did, and their kids 
wanted it more than our kids did," Crespi Coach Kevin Slattum said. 
</P>
<P>
"We just came out fired up and took them out of their game from the start with 
some tough serving and good defense," said Royal's Adam White, who had eight 
kills. 
</P>
<P>
Colton led Royal with 12 kills. Miguel Ramirez and Kevin Hambly each added 11 
kills and Travis Ferguson had 30 assists. 
</P>
<P>
Palumbo led Crespi with 10 kills. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Crespi High setter Jeff Schuberg, falling, makes a futile bid to keep 
the ball alive during the third game of Royal's nonleague victory Tuesday. 
HYUNGWON KANG / For The Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
