<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOLDEST BLADE SCORES PIMLICO UPSET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BALTIMORE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Boldest Blade took the lead entering the stretch and defeated Silly Baeder by 1 
1/4 lengths in Tuesday's $18,000 Farest Nan Purse at Pimlico Race Course. The 
winner, ridden by Gregg McCarron, ran 1 1/16 miles in 1:45 2/5 and paid $27.60. 
</P>
