<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
PRESTON'S BIG DAY LEADS MASTER'S TO 18-9 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Squeezing a season's worth of statistics into one game, Jeff Preston of The 
Master's had a day to remember in his team's 18-9 nonconference baseball win 
over Chapman at The Master's on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Preston went four for four, scored five runs, had two doubles, a triple, a home 
run (his second) and drove in seven runs to lead the rout. 
</P>
<P>
Jeff Cole was the beneficiary of Preston's outburst, picking up the win in 
relief. Joining Preston in the offensive fireworks were teammates Kevin Backes 
(three for four, four runs batted in) and Mark MacArthur (two hits, two RBIs). 
</P>
<P>
Master's improved to 10-12. 
</P>
<P>
In other baseball games: 
</P>
<P>
Glendale 7, Moorpark 6 -- Art Chute knocked in Victor Ramirez with the winning 
run on a two-out single in the bottom of the ninth against visiting Moorpark, 
which entered the game leading the Western State Conference. 
</P>
<P>
Glendale starter Matt Whisenant (4-3) pitched his way out of a one-out, 
bases-loaded jam in the top of the ninth inning to earn the win. 
</P>
<P>
Willie Leighton (4-1) went the distance for Moorpark (12-7, 7-2). 
</P>
<P>
Chute had a two-run single to spark a five-run third inning for Glendale (9-15, 
4-5). Moorpark's Don Smith hit a solo home run in the seventh, and the Raiders 
pulled into a 6-6 tie in the eighth. 
</P>
<P>
Valley 3, Bakersfield 1 -- Dan Carroll recorded the final two outs, including a 
bases-loaded strikeout to end the game, as the Monarchs held for a win in a WSC 
game at home. 
</P>
<P>
Carroll, who recorded his first save, took over for starter Colin Hines 
(7-14-2, 3-5), who struck out four and allowed three hits in 8 1/3 innings to 
earn the win. 
</P>
<P>
E. J. Pape's bases-loaded single in the third gave Valley a 1-0 lead. Vladimir 
Pajcin drove in the second run of the inning with a bases-loaded smash that the 
right fielder could not handle. 
</P>
<P>
Gene Demyon singled in the sixth to score Chris Greenamyer for Valley's third 
run. 
</P>
<P>
SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
CS Northridge 6-3, Mankato State (Minn.) 0-0 -- Debby Dickmann and Heather 
Lindstrom delivered a one-two punch for Cal State Northridge as the Lady 
Matadors punched out Mankato State (Minn.) in a nonconference doubleheader at 
Cal State Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
Dickmann, a senior, pitched a four-hitter, striking out six and walking two. 
Lindstrom, a sophomore, pitched a two-hitter with three strikeouts. 
