<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: FALSKEN CHOOSES CS LONG BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tim Falsken, a senior infielder and pitcher at Westlake High, has committed 
orally to attend Cal State Long Beach in the fall. He chose the 49ers over UCLA 
after visiting both schools. 
</P>
<P>
Falsken, 5-foot-9, 160 pounds, has played a key role in Westlake's 7-0 start 
this season, the best in school history. Falsken is batting .476 and has scored 
13 runs. In addition, he is 3-0 with an 0.53 earned-run average in 13 1/3 
innings. 
</P>
<P>
He is the second Westlake player to commit to a four-year school. Catcher Mike 
Lieberthal committed to Arizona State last month. The next signing period for 
high school seniors begins April 11. 
</P>
<P>
Jason Gudzunas of Fullerton Troy High, an All-Freeway League selection last 
season, has made an oral commitment to play football at Cal State Northridge in 
the fall. 
</P>
<P>
Gudzunas, 6-foot-2, 195 pounds, was a lineman in Troy's 5-2 defense but is 
projected as an outside linebacker at Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
"Speed was (Jason's) biggest asset," Troy Coach John Turek said. "He could 
really run to the football. He was always around the ball." 
</P>
<P>
Gudzunas had 57 tackles, five sacks and recovered four fumbles last season. He 
also led Troy's special teams in tackles. 
</P>
<P>
Matthew Carinio, a senior at Santa Clara High, finished sixth in a field of 54 
cyclists this month in the Fountain Grove Circuit Race in Santa Rosa, Calif. 
</P>
<P>
Carinio was one of 13 racers who finished the event. 
</P>
<P>
Jeff and Ernie Thorpe's J-24, Color Blind, was the overall winner in the 
spinnaker division of the Ventura Yacht Club's Frostbite Series that concluded 
earlier this month in Ventura Harbor. 
</P>
<P>
Races of two, five and 10 kilometers will start from Fallbrook Mall in West 
Hills on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The 5K run begins at 8 a.m., with the 10K and 2K runs scheduled to begin at 
8:45 and 9:45, respectively. 
</P>
<P>
Race-day registration is $15. Sponsors are the Canoga Park High Boosters Club 
and the West Valley Eagles Track Club. 
</P>
<P>
Information: 818-340-5158. 
</P>
<P>
Basketball tryouts for the North American Maccabiah Youth Games' Los Angeles 
entry will be held Sunday at Montclair Prep's gymnasium from 9 a.m to 11 a.m. 
The Games will be held in Detroit from Aug. 19-26 and are open to Jewish boys 
and girls under 17 years of age. 
</P>
<P>
Information: 213-938-2531, ext. 240. 
</P>
