<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL COACH AT BREA-OLINDA QUITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS FOSTER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rick Jones has resigned as boys' basketball coach at Brea-Olinda High School. 
</P>
<P>
"I cannot teach world history effectively, be in the classroom and direct a 
total (basketball) program," Jones said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
"It's too much for one person." 
</P>
<P>
Jones, a four-year coach, said his letter of resignation will be submitted to 
the Brea-Olinda school board tonight. 
</P>
<P>
Jones, who has taught world history at Brea-Olinda for 16 years, was a junior 
varsity coach and varsity assistant at Brea-Olinda for nine seasons. He 
replaced Gene Lloyd as basketball coach after the 1984-85 season. 
</P>
<P>
Jones was 79-31 during his four seasons. The Wildcats won three Orange League 
championships and finished second once. They also reached the quarterfinals of 
the Southern Section playoffs twice. CHRIS FOSTER 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
