<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASEBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
ROSAS PITCHES SANTA ANA TO VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STUART MATTHEWS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jesse Rosas was the winning pitcher in Santa Ana High School's 4-2 Century 
League baseball victory over Foothill Tuesday at Foothill. 
</P>
<P>
But it wasn't easy. 
</P>
<P>
Rosas (3-2) threw more than 100 pitches and walked six but finished with a 
three-hitter. He needed only 68 pitches Friday at Canyon, but lost, 2-1. 
</P>
<P>
"Jesse was all over the place today," Santa Ana Coach Bill Ross said. "But I 
guess he threw it in the right places at the right times." 
</P>
<P>
Foothill also hit the ball at the right people at the right times for Santa 
Ana. That often meant within diving range of Octavio Medina, Santa Ana's 
slick-fielding shortstop. 
</P>
<P>
With two outs in the first, Medina sprawled to his right to knock down a 
chopper by Shawn Sousa, and threw in time to retire Sousa. 
</P>
<P>
In the second, Medina turned an acrobatic double play to help Rosas out of 
trouble again. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana got just enough timely hitting. Trailing, 2-1, in the third, Santa 
Ana tied the score when Rosas drove in Bill Johnson with a single to center. 
</P>
<P>
In the fourth, Medina and Jeff Fuentes walked with two outs, and both scored on 
John Morales' line single up the middle. That gave Santa Ana the lead for good. 
</P>
<P>
Both teams are 4-4 overall, 1-1 in league. STUART MATTHEWS 
</P>
</TEXT>
