<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
COLBY HELPS RANCHO SANTIAGO POUND ORANGE COAST, 15-4 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Conrad Colby had four hits, scored two runs and drove in two runs to lead 
Rancho Santiago College to a 15-4 victory over Orange Coast in an Orange Empire 
Conference baseball game Tuesday at Rancho Santiago. 
</P>
<P>
Rob Reimers had three hits, scored three runs and had two RBIs, and Steve Grack 
had three hits, including two doubles and two RBIs, for Rancho Santiago (17-5, 
7-3). The Dons had 17 hits. 
</P>
<P>
Matt Lackie (6-2) allowed 11 hits but went the distance for the victory. John 
Douris took the loss for OCC (9-13, 2-7). 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 5, Golden West 3 -- Doug McConathy had five singles and an RBI for 
visiting Cypress (13-11, 2-7). Terry Tewell had three hits and two RBIs and Tom 
Puppe had two hits for Cypress. Brian Mena had two hits and Gary Christopherson 
had a two-run single in the sixth for Golden West (15-5, 6-4), which left 16 
runners on base. 
</P>
<P>
Riverside 14, Fullerton 1 -- Ben Blomdahl (8-1) allowed six hits, struck out 
eight and gave up one unearned run for visiting Riverside (18-6, 7-3). Tom 
Kelly (5-1) took the loss for Fullerton (16-4, 7-2). Riverside scored nine runs 
and sent 14 batters to the plate in the third inning. 
</P>
<P>
In a nonconference baseball game: 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback 14, Washington Bellevue 2 -- Buster Nietzke and Neil Carter each had 
three hits for host Saddleback (8-10). Ralph Grajeda hit a home run and Corey 
Guliano (3-3) pitched the first six innings for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
In Orange Empire Conference tennis: 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback 8, Riverside 1 -- Host Saddleback swept in doubles. Carl Hands and 
Stan Sanders won, 6-1, 6-3, Arlen Sternberg and Scott Hansen won, 6-1, 6-4, and 
Eimei Ishida and Scott Clark won, 6-2, 6-3, for Saddleback (13-0, 6-0). 
</P>
<P>
Orange Coast 9, Fullerton 0 -- The No. 2 doubles team of Chris Flood and Robert 
Van Duyne won, 6-0, 6-0, for host Orange Coast (10-1, 6-1). 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 9, Golden West 0 -- John Swaino won, 3-6, 6-3, 6-4, and Bob Carlton 
won, 7-6, 6-0, for host Cypress (7-5, 4-2). 
</P>
<P>
In Orange Empire Conference women's tennis: 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback 8, Riverside 1 -- Noelle Schmidt defeated Lisa Goolsby, 6-0, 6-1, to 
lead Saddleback (5-1 in the conference) at Riverside. 
</P>
</TEXT>
