<P>
EYE SURGERY IDLES ROY ACUFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NASHVILLE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Roy Acuff will be away from the Grand Ole Opry stage for two to three weeks 
because of minor eye surgery, a spokeswoman said today. 
</P>
<P>
Acuff, 86, had outpatient surgery Monday on his right eye to prevent his 
glaucoma from getting worse, said Opry spokeswoman Debbie Logue. She said the 
singer will wear an eye patch for a while. Acuff, dubbed the King of Country 
Music, has performed at the Opry since 1938. 
</P>
